<br>
Instead of reducing the bolt and rain mitigation rates, I've added a base mitigation rate for standard DD's.  My goal is as follows:<br>
<br>
20% more damage mitigated from rain spells than direct-damage spells. (mainly from resists)<br>
<br>
5% more damage mitigated from bolts than direct-damage spells. (mainly from misses, 1 miss in 20 attempts).<br>
<br>
5% base resist rate for ALL nukes.<br>
<br>
For a total of 5% for DD, 10% for bolts, and 25% for rains.  This agrees with the <br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=24601.topic" target="top">Rain Resist Study</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> from Graffe's and with Belhaven's posted statistics (thank you kindly).<br>
<br>
The main thing left for debate now is the 5% base resist rate.  Does anyone know of any studies done regarding this?  I image it would be very difficult because of varying resistances of mobs.  5% seems reasonable to me, and also agrees with rain resist calculations (25% average resist - 20% innate rain resist (from lure study) gives 5% resist based on actual resistances).<br>
<br>
I've also corrected the ear focus effectiveness -- instead of 15%, I am listing 7.5% (variable from 0 to 15%).  Note that doing this had a pretty severe effect on the actual DPM values (though no effect at all on relative values).<br>
<br>
Any comments?<br>
<br>
- Nemuneir Noldaron<br>
Arch-Convoker of Vallis Aspectus<br>
